        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 330 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Panola, or 10 miles southwest of Aliceville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tuscaloosa, Northport, Eutaw, Aliceville, Gordo, Reform, Carrollton,
Pickensville, Holt, Moundville, Coaling, Coker, Akron, Union,
Memphis, McMullen, Panola, West Greene, McFarland Mall, and Benevola.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
